text: The Trump administration is preparing a policy shift that could make it more difficult for immigrants from countries covered by the President's travel ban to obtain green cards and other immigration benefits.  According to internal Department of Homeland Security documents quoted by The New York Times, US Citizenship and Immigration Services (USCIS) would treat "country-specific factors" outlined in the travel ban as "significant negative factors" when assessing a range of immigration applications.

Bihar Election ECI Result 2025: The National Democratic Alliance (NDA) won 202 seats in the Bihar Assembly Elections, results for which was announced by the Election Commission of India (ECI) on Friday. The NDA had scored 206 seats in the 2010 assembly elections and fell short of the historic tally by just four seats this time. Notably, during the counting, the NDA's lead once surged to 208 seats, but it finally settled for 202 seats as the BJP won 89 seats, JDU 85, LJPRV 19, HAM 5, and RLM 4.
